   \textbackslash{}usepackage\{upgreek\}
   \textbackslash{}setlength\{\textbackslash{}oddsidemargin\}\{-69pt\}
   \textbackslash{}begin\{document\}\$\$n=418\$\$\textbackslash{}end\{docum
   ent\}) as a case study, XGBoost achieved the highest discrimination
   (AUROC = 0.95) and robust calibration across probability thresholds,
   while ensemble models demonstrated superior stability compared to linear
   baselines. SHAP analysis identified bilirubin, prothrombin time,
   follow-up duration, and age as dominant predictors, consistent with
   hepatology insights. By integrating calibration, transparency, and
   reproducibility, this pipeline offers a generalized framework for
   clinical prognosis tasks beyond cirrhosis and supports reliable
   deployment of machine learning in clinical decision support systems.},
